---
/**
 * Tracker methodology — the primary E-E-A-T page for the legality dataset.
 * Editorial-independence statement, sourcing hierarchy, update cadence,
 * verification protocol, and correction policy. No affiliate links.
 */
export const prerender = true;

import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR_ID, ORG_ID } from '../../lib/schema';

const ORIGIN = 'https://sweepstakeswiz.com';
const canonicalPath = '/sweepstakes-tracker/methodology/';
const canonical = `${ORIGIN}${canonicalPath}`;

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
  { name: 'Sweepstakes Tracker', path: '/sweepstakes-tracker/' },
  { name: 'Methodology', path: canonicalPath },
];

const articleLd = {
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${canonical}#article`,
  headline: 'How the Sweepstakes Legality Tracker works',
  description:
    'Sourcing hierarchy, update cadence, verification protocol, and correction policy for the Sweepstakes Wiz US legality dataset.',
  mainEntityOfPage: { '@id': `${canonical}#webpage` },
  inLanguage: 'en-US',
  author: { '@id': AUTHOR_ID },
  publisher: { '@id': ORG_ID },
};

const pyramidImageNode = {
  '@type': 'ImageObject',
  '@id': `${canonical}#source-tier-pyramid`,
  contentUrl: `${ORIGIN}/images/sweepstakes-tracker/sweepstakes-tracker-source-tier-pyramid.svg`,
  width: 960,
  height: 560,
  caption:
    'Four-tier sourcing hierarchy behind the SweepstakesWiz legality tracker plus the four-step verification workflow that gates any status change on human editorial sign-off. Source: SweepstakesWiz Tracker Methodology, July 2026.',
  creator: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'SweepstakesWiz' },
  creditText: 'SweepstakesWiz',
};
---
<ContentLayout
  title="Tracker Methodology — Sourcing, Cadence & Verification"
  description="How Sweepstakes Wiz compiles and verifies US sweepstakes casino legality data: source tiers, daily update cadence, human review, and corrections. Editorially independent."
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  heroTitle="Tracker methodology"
  heroSubtitle="How we compile, verify, and correct the US sweepstakes legality dataset."
  mainEntityId={`${canonical}#article`}
  jsonLd={[articleLd, pyramidImageNode]}
>
  <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
  <p>
    The Sweepstakes Legality Tracker is published by Sweepstakes Wiz, which also
    operates commercial casino reviews. The tracker is editorially independent of
    that review business: it carries <strong>no affiliate links</strong>, accepts
    no operator funding for placement, and its legal-status labels are never
    influenced by commercial relationships. Where our commercial pages suppress
    affiliate promotion for legal reasons, this tracker still reports the neutral
    legal status of each jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2>Sourcing hierarchy</h2>
  <p>We weight sources in this order, and never change a status label on a single low-tier source alone:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Tier 1 — Official government.</strong> State legislatures, attorney-general offices, gaming commissions, and court records (via LegiScan bill tracking and primary filings).</li>
    <li><strong>Tier 2 — Tier-1 journalism.</strong> AP, Reuters, and comparable outlets with published editorial standards.</li>
    <li><strong>Tier 3 — Industry trade press</strong> with editorial standards.</li>
    <li><strong>Tier 4 — Other sources</strong> used only as corroboration, never as the sole basis for a change.</li>
  </ol>

  <figure class="mt-figure" role="group" aria-labelledby="mt-pyramid-cap">
    <img
      src="/images/sweepstakes-tracker/sweepstakes-tracker-source-tier-pyramid.svg"
      alt="Four-tier source pyramid: government, tier-one journalism, trade press, other; label changes require human sign-off."
      width="960"
      height="560"
      loading="lazy"
      decoding="async"
    />
    <figcaption id="mt-pyramid-cap">
      The four-tier sourcing hierarchy plus the four-step verification workflow behind every status change.
      <strong>Source:</strong> SweepstakesWiz Tracker Methodology, July 2026.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2>Update cadence</h2>
  <p>
    The dataset refreshes <strong>daily</strong> via an automated pipeline that pulls
    LegiScan bill activity and vetted news feeds. Each state row records both a
    <em>last auto-updated</em> and a <em>last reviewed</em> timestamp. Our coverage
    target is to review at least 70% of jurisdictions within any 7-day window.
  </p>

  <h2>Verification protocol</h2>
  <p>Two tracks keep automation honest:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>News events</strong> are auto-classified and published with a confidence score; low-confidence items are flagged for review before they surface.</li>
    <li><strong>Status changes</strong> (a state moving between legal, gray, restricted, pending-ban, or banned) are <strong>always human-gated</strong>. A change requires a Tier-1 or Tier-2 source and editorial sign-off before the label updates.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Confidence levels</h2>
  <p>
    Each state carries a confidence rating (high / medium / low) reflecting how
    settled its legal posture is. Actively contested or fast-moving states are
    marked lower confidence even when a current label is assigned.
  </p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>
    We correct errors promptly and transparently. If you believe a status,
    source, or bill is wrong, contact
    <a href="/contact/">our editorial team</a>. Substantive corrections are
    reflected in the affected state's timestamps.
  </p>

  <h2>License &amp; citation</h2>
  <p>
    The dataset is published under
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">CC-BY 4.0</a>.
    You may reuse it with attribution to Sweepstakes Wiz. Machine-readable
    endpoints are documented on the <a href="/sweepstakes-tracker/api/">API page</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-byline">
    Maintained by <a href="/author/ilija-milosevic/">Ilija Milosevic</a>. This page is
    editorial analysis of public law &mdash; not legal advice. See our
    <a href="/editorial-policy/">editorial policy</a>.
  </p>

  <style>
    .content-card h2{color:#0a1628;margin-top:28px;}
    .content-card ol,.content-card ul{padding-left:22px;}
    .content-card li{margin:8px 0;line-height:1.6;}
    .mt-byline{font-size:.85rem;color:#64748b;border-top:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding-top:14px;margin-top:26px;}
    .mt-byline a{color:#b45309;font-weight:600;}
    .mt-figure{margin:18px 0 24px;}
    .mt-figure img{display:block;width:100%;height:auto;max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;}
    .mt-figure figcaption{font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748b;margin-top:10px;text-align:center;line-height:1.5;}
  </style>
</ContentLayout>
